=>What is SHELL?
	it is provide an environment to a user to execute commands and interact with kernel.

=>There are different type of shell.
	bash, sh, ksh, tsh, fish, zsh.

=> you can check your shell by #echo $0
=> which shell is present in your distro #cat /etc/shells
=> What is ahell script?
	it is set of command execute sequentially.
=>Basic Script
	#!/bin/bash
	echo "hello world!"
=> How to Run a Script?
	make sure it has execute permission.
	$chmod 777 <filename>
	./script.sh
	/path/script.sh
	bash script.sh

	ctrl+c to terminate
	ctrl+z to stop
